The Ogun State Government has ordered the immediate closure of the COVID-19 test laboratory in Olabisi Onabanjo University Teaching Hospital after about 32 staff tested positive for the virus. The hospital commenced sample testing without adequate protective gear for staff, putting them at great risk of contracting the virus. Ogun State Governor Dapo Abiodun SaharaReporters had reported that 32 positive cases have been recorded among the staff with one death recorded. See Also






